theorem
  M1 is_congruent_Matrix_of M2 & n>0 implies M2 is_congruent_Matrix_of
  M1
proof
  assume that
A1: M1 is_congruent_Matrix_of M2 and
A2: n>0;
  consider M be Matrix of n,K such that
A3: M is invertible and
A4: M1=M@*M2*M by A1,Def6;
